## This file contains the ideas for this specific project

# Requirements

1. Should work with any BMLT by setting up the server information 
2. Should use the api-mapper for the project
3. Each homegroup should have a page
4. Should have a page robust and efficient search page
5. Should allow users to store a cookie that keeps track of their home location/area and uses it to load the main schedule viewer page when they visit
6. Needs to be able to produce calendar event objects for download that can be used in Google, outlook, and Apple 
7. Should have a subscription producing events calendar and/or celebration calendar based on selectable level of structure (area, region, etc)
8. Top-line aesthetics
9. Accessibility first
10. Cognitive load driven design
    1. Color coded days of the week
    2. Focused emphasis on important data
    3. Aria-enabled DOM 
11. Hopefully use open maps for free

# Home Group Page Details

1. Have individual meeting cards
2. A mini map 

# Desirable Upgrades

1. Email server that sends daily calendar digests based on area selected
2. Use email to create user. 
    1. Login via emailed code - no password 
3. Send to map app on mobile for meetings